The paper discusses the design of ranking models that can anticipate and avoid undesirable long-term consequences, which involves understanding user dynamics and optimizing for both immediate utility and long-term welfare. This suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques for modeling and optimization, as well as information retrieval (cs.IR) for ranking algorithms. The paper also touches on social implications and discourse (cs.SI, cs.SOC), indicating a broader societal context for the research.
